net.trajano.auth.session

Class TestServerAuthModule

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.trajano.auth.session.TestServerAuthModule
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    javax.security.auth.message.config.ServerAuthContext, javax.security.auth.message.module.ServerAuthModule, javax.security.auth.message.ServerAuth

    public class TestServerAuthModule
extends Object
implements javax.security.auth.message.module.ServerAuthModule, javax.security.auth.message.config.ServerAuthContext

    This is a JASPIC ServerAuthModule used for testing purposes.

    The module will detect if the user is not yet authenticated to a simple web form that asks for a user name. It forms a subject with the pattern 

     https://[username]@test-server-auth-module

    The module does uses HttpSession to store the data subject and nonce data.

    Author:
    Archimedes Trajano
